column5: As you can tell, very wet. We stayed out all day, seems like no matter how much rain gear you wear you eventually get wet. Again lots of small Perch. About every 20 caught 1 keeper. Sunday was better. We saw 1 tag Perch caught beside us by a little girl with her family. You could have heard the excitement across the lake. They pulled anchor and they were gone to the headquarters. Came back an hour latter and anchored. $500.00 tag we could hear the kids say. As of yesterday 15 tags caught. Here's a few pictures.  Our buddys trying to stay dry       Couldn't resist, "My Pose"
Wow. lots of boats out. Great pose you got there. Next time, photoshop the background to make it look more authentic.
Couldn't resist, "My Pose"   LOL... Mike has started a serious trend...too funny!!

Roy, coffee out my nose.  My buddy said I was a sick puppy  I expect a call from Spiel. Gezzz that didn't take long, did you see me typing. You like my CTC boutique Rain Wear autographed with Perch white spooch
Kennyman, did you get my PM.? Say hy to your dad for me.
Hey hey hey! When have I ever photoshopped a background?  Glad to see I have such influence though!  Here's a tip. Next time extend your arms to the max, it makes the fish look grotesquely huge.
